content: a must have. very accurate and super helpful! thanks guys
Hard to set location, small graph, no landsape display, cannot swipe to next day.

The best layout of any of the tide apps that I have tried. Very responsive developer. would be a strong five star if the tables were available offline like the ios version. definitely worth the small cost.

(edit) Devs listened to suggestions, end results with new version is fantastic. Having the recent searches available is perfect. Can't wait for what is up to come for androids. Thanks for caring! This app is a Solid ðŸŒŸðŸŒŸðŸŒŸðŸŒŸðŸŒŸ (used in the Pacific Northwest, USA) Samsung Galaxy Note8
replyContent: Version 1.3 has search, GPS detection, meters/feet, 12/14 hour time, and several other minor improvements. Thanks again for the suggestions.

content: Brainware fix every issue I found. This Android version is now as good as the IOS iPad version. I now want the Pro version to get released for Android cell phones. Thanks Brian
Really wish charts were available offline. The iPhone version is so much better, let's hope the Android version catches up. As it stands now, not useful.
12-hour time? What am I, planning a brunch around the tides? 24 hour time. Also didn't seem to have a way to pick closest port for tide data. I had to scroll up the cost like Lord Vancouver.
replyContent: Both of your suggestions have been now implemented in version 1.3. To change to 24-hour time, just tap on the time (just below the date) on the graph screen. To find the closest port, select Locate in the upper left above the map. Email me if you have any more suggestions.

content: Android version is weak on features compared to iPhone version. Interface could be much more intuitive. In the tide chart, days of the week do not match up with the monthly calendar days. Users should be able to set a default tide location.
replyContent: Version 1.3 now has meters/feet, 12-hour/24-hour times, GPS location detection, and a fixed monthly calendar which also lets you choose a date. More suggestions welcome!

content: Best tide app ever helps with everything
I cannot load this app, very annoying
replyContent: v1.1 now available which should fix the problem.

content: I have been waiting for this app to become available on android.  It's consistently accurate and intuitive to use.  There is no better tide app, I have tried them all.

I like the app, but am wondering what the features are on the iPhone that aren't on Android yet. For example, why doesnt the date refresh to the current date when I reopen the app?? I have tried the usual tricks to refresh but nothing seems to work, other than manually selecting the date.
replyContent: You suggested, and v1.1 fixes both of these issues. Thank you for pointing them out.

content: Replacement for broken NOAA app. Has everything I need for planning fishing trips. I wish there were moon phases like the iOS version and settings for increasing table, map, and graph sizes to optimize for tablets, but it works so I hope any new features don't break it.
Good but waiting for all the features of the Apple version.
replyContent: V1.1 adds new *Android only* feet/meter option. And you can now delete recent locations, automatically changes date when loaded, and saves locations for all android devices now. No in-app purchases needed. All free updates.

content: This is the one app I miss from my iPhone days....  I am so happy to see it come to Android!  Buy this app so he can port all the great features to this platform, even as is it's the best thing in the Android marketplace!
